        <TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" WIDTH=693 HEIGHT=133 COLSPAN=3>
                    
                      <div align="left">
                      <table border="0" width="696" height="136">
                        <tr><td width='686' height='19' valign='top' align='left'> <font face='Arial,sans-serif' SIZE=2 COLOR=#ffff80> 2000-07-06 - Pending Server Split</font> </td></tr><tr><td width='686' height='19'></td></tr><tr><td width='686' height='19' valign='top' align='left'> <font face='Arial,sans-serif' SIZE=2 COLOR=#C0C0C0> <u><b>Gorden post on pending server split:</b></u>
<p><i>Doesnt look like anyone has copied it over, so here goes:</i></p>
<p><i>July 5th, 4:00pm<br>
-----------------</i>
<p><i>*Karana, Bertox, and Test Server Split*</i>
<p><i>Hello all,</i>
<p><i>At some time between 6pm and 8pm PDT (GMT-8), we will open /movelog
registration on Karana, Bertox, and Test, to allow players on those servers to
request that their account be moved to the new split-server, Terris-Thule.
Players on the affected servers will be informed via server broadcast when
registration is open. Players wishing to have their characters moved to the new
split server will need to run the command &quot;/movelog yes&quot; after
registration is opened.</i>
<p><i>Notes:</i>
<p><i>- /movelog only needs to be run from ONE character, and will count for all
characters on that server on that account.<br>
- Players who have requested a move should make sure all of their corpses are
looted by the time the server is brought down tomorrow morning (9am PDT).
Corpses will not be duplicated in the new world, and anything left on a corpse
left behind by anyone who moves will be lost.<br>
- We may or may not be able to move everyone who requests this action, based
upon the number of total requests that we receive.<br>
- The GM/Guide staff will not be able to tell you whether or not you have been
selected until after the move is actually completed.<br>
- Test Server Players with artificially buffed characters on their account
*MUST* delete those characters prior to registering for move. Having
artificially buffed characters moved to the live servers will result in action
against the players account.</i>
<p><i><br>
*Item Changes Pending in Next Patch*</i>
<p><i>In the next patch, keys for Charasis, Sebilis, and Howling Stones will all
be made NODROP if not currently set with that flag. This means that people
holding more than one key will not be able to hand out their extras after the
patch.</i>
<p><i>At the same time that this change is made, we are also implementing a new
change that &quot;binds&quot; these items to your character. Should you die with
one of these keys in your possession, it will not be left on your corpse, but
will stay with you when you return to your bindpoint.</i>
<p><i>This change was made in light of the difficulty of the key-quests, in
order to eliminate the need to do the quest multiple times prior to entering the
dungeon.</i>
<p><i><br>
-The EverQuest Team</i></p>
<p><b><u>A later post provides an update:</u></b></p>
<u>&gt;&gt;&gt;In the next patch, keys for Charasis, Sebilis, and Howling Stones
will all be made NODROP if not currently set with that flag.&quot; *ahem*
Howling Stones IS Charasis..(it has two names for some reason)</u>
<p><u>Ack! Well I meant Veeshans Peak. Of course, keys for Sebilis and VP are
already NODROP, so the main concern was Charasis (Howling Stones). So I guess I
got it covered. </u>
<p><u>-Gordon</u></p>
<p><i><u><br>
